Driven by a team of world-class machine learning experts, Themis AI developed Capsa to equip AI professionals with the feedback they need to de-risk their models. Capsa can surgically update the architecture of any model within seconds so that the model can quantify its own uncertainty. With Capsa, AI models can flag their own mistakes and hallucinations, unlocking AI’s potential across new industries while enabling quality assurance. Capsa makes developing and running safe AI models less expensive and more efficient, saving on costly AI chips and cloud computing and decreasing time to market. As Themis AI continues to grow, it aims to make its state-of-the-art advancements in safe and reliable AI accessible to machine learning engineers and customers around the world. AI is a forecast machine to a fault. How confident should you be in the AI that serves you and your customers? Themis AI’s Capsa can tell you.

Memory-Augmented Sales Agent Embedded within Gmail, Salesforce, and Slack, this agent continuously analyzes deal state and team context to recommend timely interventions, such as reaching out to an economic buyer, complete with a drafted email already waiting in your inbox. 	2.	Deal Risk Detection Engine A fine-tuned model trained on your company’s historical deals and customer conversations (CRM, email, and call transcripts), scoring active opportunities and surfacing interpretable risk factors - giving leaders visibility and control before pipeline slips. 	3.	Real-Time Coaching Layer A coaching layer that listens to live videoconferencing calls and triggers contextual cue cards — such as battle cards, talk tracks, or discovery questions — based on conversational intent and flow. Copilot is trusted by high-performing mid-market and enterprise teams, and built for secure, compliant, and deeply integrated deployment across your GTM teams.

We believe AI is most effective when it can collaborate with people, merging their creativity and institutional knowledge with the scalability of machines. Their product, Salem, is an AI-based cyber analyst designed to increase the number of alert investigations your organization can perform. Salem runs a tier 1 and 2-style investigation on the 100’s or 1000’s of alerts that are too noisy to go into your SOC, and then escalates back the handful that are most likely to be actual cyber threats. By running in some cases 100x or more investigations, Salem gives you the opportunity to identify threats that might have previously flown under the radar, leading to a decreased time-to-detect and an increased ROI of other cyber detection tech you’ve invested in. Yes Collective is transforming mental healthcare for parents with the first-of-its-kind digital mental wellness platform that solves the interconnected problems of modern family life through coach-led guidance, step-by-step practice, and community support. Our collective is an expert team of doctors, therapists, psychologists, and behavioral health coaches who translate cutting-edge science and expert wisdom on all facets of parent mental health & wellness into actionable, simple, and effective tools for self-healing and multi-generational wellbeing. We combine parent-focused expert knowledge and practice into a mobile ecosystem of AI-assisted emotional fitness coaching, live therapist-led events, daily articles and recordings from the experts, and a private, facilitated social network just for parents. Yes Collective is stepping up to transform mental and emotional healthcare for all parents by making expert therapeutic tools, practices, and one-on-one support accessible, bringing expert care right into their back pockets. We’re helping families become happier and healthier, one parent at a time.

Name: Worddio: Vocabualry builder
Description: Worddio is an AI-driven vocabulary-building app. We are growing our user base at a rapid pace because we offer our customers: - The unique feature to learn words without touching their smartphone. - 34 languages that cover 90% of the world's population. Our in-house AI/ML models help us in: - Building individual learning paths. - Optimizing marketing costs. - Deep user database segmentation (psychological, behavioral, and interests based) Customer Problem The main problem we face is the language barrier between peoples. This specifically applies to EU as a multi-lingual community. From other hand the biggest challenge for learning a foreign language is time. Advanced online technologies provide many learning opportunities but all of them require 100% focus for a long period of time which many people do not have. Products & Services To solve this problem, we turned the flashcards that students often use to memorize words into audio flashcards. Over 2000 people say that Worddio is a great tool for learning new words. With Worddio you can learn new words on the move or while doing something else, without touching your phone. Through this method, the learner will also memorize the pronunciation in the correct way, spoken by a native language speaker. We safe students time! Target Market The Worddio app is designed specifically for people learning a foreign language and who don't have time to learn and memorize new words. The Global Online Language Learning Market was valued at $12.49 billion in 2019 and is projected to reach $25.73 billion by 2027. With its 34 languages Worddio has potential usefulness for over 90% of the world population. Does it work? We have more than 200K installations and more than 1300 paying users. Business Model - subscriptions: 1, 3, 6 and 12 months, lifetime - up-sales of premium content - advanced flashcards by topics, Audiobooks and Podcasts. - Ads - general or targeted based on user profiles - Apply data & technology to other platforms/apps/fields . . . Developing a B2C model on a global level takes time and resources to break even, but once that happens, the return on investment is maximized at scale. Customer Segments Professionals: adults looking to improve their foreign-language skills for business or career reasons Casual learners: travelers, expats, or other persons wishing to learn a new language or enhance their current knowledge Sector-specific: Service workers, such as call-center staff or healthcare workers, who can perform better with a larger vocabulary and accurate pronunciation. Youth: 12-20 year-olds studying secondary languages in schools Sales & Marketing Strategy We have technology that allows us to build psychological profiles and predict users' behaviours without accessing their sensitive data. We can build bespoke learning paths, custom sales funnels, and target ads. The data gathered allow the pursue of three main objectives: optimzing marketing resources by leveraging predictive machine learning models creating individual learning paths based on users needs upsale of particular content or products Competitors The language learning apps space looks crowded but in fact there is a specific empty niche - passive learning. There are a lot of language learning apps on the market, but none of them use a passive learning method to save time for their users - Worddio is the only one that does. We are opening a new market group to support language learning. The Worddio app is a pseudo-passive learning app powered by AI which saves student time. Competitive Advantage Worddio main advantages are: - our app’s passive learning method  - huge stock of professionally recorded audio-flashcards in 34 languages. - scientific-based approach that leverages ML and AI to optimize costs and improve user experience - premium content section - AI features that will help us deliver the ultimate hands-free experience to our users.
